info.name: Gmail - Mac OSX
info.description:
A complete Mac-style makeover of Gmail: buttons, sidebar, and all. 

<<< Look at the pictures. I have a lot.
Based on the native Mail client found on Macintosh machines, this theme for Gmail creates a familiar yet unique webmail experience. The first of its kind in quality, design, and functionality. Look no further, your ultimate theme lies here. IMPORTANT: Remember to change theme to Light Gray (okay, others are fine too but may not look good) And remember to rate: I'd love to hear your feedback so I can improve my userstyles.
info.additionalInfo:
Changelog

1.2.13 - Adds prefixes for cross-browser support 1.2.11 - Fixed more Compact & Contacts bugs 1.2.6 - New CSS multi-gradient window operator buttons (on compose window). Actually looks like Mac OSX. 1.2.3 - Styled compose tab action buttons (minimize, pop-out, close) 1.1.2.8 - Fixed a lot of minor bugs w/ vertical split view 1.1.2 - Adds support for Compact view 1.1.1 - Fixes a lot of Contacts bugs. 1.1 - No more need for userscript: now uses latest CSS3 pseudo-classes to change content 1.0 - Initial release
